WEBVTT

00:02.830 --> 00:04.420
Katie: You got to love public
school -- free babysitting

00:04.420 --> 00:06.880
and a convenient place to
throw away my car garbage.

00:06.880 --> 00:09.290
Tara: You ruined
my son's life!

00:09.290 --> 00:11.210
Ah, Tara Summers --

00:11.210 --> 00:12.710
my daughter's boyfriend's
mother.

00:12.710 --> 00:14.920
If I had one free punch
for anyone in the world,

00:14.920 --> 00:16.710
it would be Bryant Gumbel.

00:16.710 --> 00:19.670
But if I had two,
it would be Tara Summers.

00:19.670 --> 00:22.250
Eyo doesn't want to be an
anesthesiologist anymore.

00:22.250 --> 00:23.880
He wants to be
a cartoon artist.

00:23.880 --> 00:25.500
Mm.
He spends the day
at your house,

00:25.500 --> 00:27.500
and now he wants to
"follow his dreams."

00:27.500 --> 00:29.380
Sounds like
a real bad seed.

00:29.380 --> 00:31.210
Hi, Mom.
Hi, honey.

00:31.210 --> 00:34.000
Mama, can Autumn and I
have a playdate?

00:34.000 --> 00:36.330
[ Scoffs ]
Why must all of our children
insist on getting along?

00:36.330 --> 00:38.250
Of course you can,
sweetie.

00:38.250 --> 00:39.580
-Yay!
-Yay!

00:39.580 --> 00:42.120
Fine. But it has to
be at my house.

00:42.120 --> 00:43.790
If Autumn spends a day with you,
she'll come back wanting

00:43.790 --> 00:45.540
to be something awful
when she grows up --

00:45.540 --> 00:47.210
like a teacher.

00:47.210 --> 00:48.670
Come on.

00:48.670 --> 00:51.420
Hey, Mom, is cool if I catch a
ride home with my friends today?

00:52.880 --> 00:56.380
Yes. And nice job joining
the popular clique.

00:56.380 --> 00:57.580
Did you know I was
the most popular girl

00:57.580 --> 00:59.040
in a high school
of 5,000 people?

00:59.040 --> 01:01.250
I did, because you
talk about it constantly.

01:01.250 --> 01:04.460
Well! Somebody
sounds jealous.

01:04.460 --> 01:06.080
Have you seen Oliver?

01:06.080 --> 01:07.620
Yeah, he took the bus
to ballet practice.

01:07.620 --> 01:09.120
Mm.

01:09.120 --> 01:12.210
I've been seen talking to
my mom for a really long time,

01:12.210 --> 01:14.500
so I'm gonna go while
I still have friends.

01:14.500 --> 01:16.420
Mm.

01:16.420 --> 01:18.710
Bye, Taylor!
Have fun!

01:18.710 --> 01:21.210
First day without your blankie!
I'm so proud of you!

01:23.040 --> 01:25.880
Is it possible I came to school
for nothing?

01:25.880 --> 01:28.790
I've achieved what every
stay-at-home mom dreams of --

01:28.790 --> 01:30.790
a free afternoon.

01:30.790 --> 01:32.960
I'm going to Target to
sit on the lawn furniture!

01:36.250 --> 01:39.880
♪♪

01:39.880 --> 01:41.790
[ Hans Gruber oinking ]

01:41.790 --> 01:44.330
So that's why I was never picked
first for any team sports.

01:44.330 --> 01:46.460
Anyways,
thanks for listening.

01:47.750 --> 01:48.620
[ Door closes ]

01:48.620 --> 01:49.960
Katie.

01:49.960 --> 01:51.500
Shouldn't you be picking up
Oliver from ballet?

01:51.500 --> 01:53.920
Oh, crap! I forgot.

01:53.920 --> 01:55.420
I'm still a little
disoriented

01:55.420 --> 01:57.120
from getting woken up
from my Target nap.

01:57.120 --> 01:59.120
If they don't want you to put
three lawn chairs together

01:59.120 --> 02:00.960
to form a bed,
there should be a sign.

02:00.960 --> 02:02.830
You got to be careful,
or they will ban you.

02:02.830 --> 02:05.960
Way ahead of you.
I rotate Targets.
Hm.

02:05.960 --> 02:07.330
I got to go
pick up Oliver.
No, no, no.

02:07.330 --> 02:08.750
Before you leave,

02:08.750 --> 02:10.420
I'm doing a reading of my
soon-to-be-published book,

02:10.420 --> 02:11.830
"John Stuart Mill
and the Consequences

02:11.830 --> 02:13.170
of a Thoroughgoing
Empiricist Outlook" --

02:13.170 --> 02:14.960
I just like saying it --

02:14.960 --> 02:16.880
and I need some help
choosing a passage.

02:18.460 --> 02:19.920
Now, this passage

02:19.920 --> 02:21.960
about his marriage
to Harriet Taylor works,

02:21.960 --> 02:24.500
but feels a little nichey.
Don't you think it's nichey?

02:24.500 --> 02:25.960
So nichey.
Yeah.

02:25.960 --> 02:27.710
So then, I considered
this passage

02:27.710 --> 02:29.830
about when Mill was
the colonial administrator

02:29.830 --> 02:31.170
in the British East India
Company,

02:31.170 --> 02:32.250
but then I thought --
you don't put

02:32.250 --> 02:34.170
"Luke, I am your father"
in the trailer.

02:34.170 --> 02:36.580
No, you do not.
[ Chuckles ]

02:36.580 --> 02:38.920
So I was wondering,
what's your favorite passage?

02:40.080 --> 02:42.210
Gosh, honey.

02:42.210 --> 02:45.670
There are just so many
that I love.
Aww.

02:45.670 --> 02:47.580
The first one,
obviously.

02:47.580 --> 02:48.580
Mm-hmm.

02:48.580 --> 02:53.580
And the second one...
is just...

02:58.120 --> 03:00.460
You haven't read
my book, have you?

03:00.460 --> 03:02.210
You know if it doesn't
come in magazine form

03:02.210 --> 03:03.290
and have pictures
of celebrities,

03:03.290 --> 03:04.750
I have no chance
of staying awake.

03:06.330 --> 03:08.710
I can't read this right now.
I got to go pick up Oliver.

03:08.710 --> 03:10.120
And they say
tired driving

03:10.120 --> 03:12.040
is just as bad
as drunk driving.

03:12.040 --> 03:13.210
Do you support
drunk driving, Greg?

03:14.750 --> 03:16.080
I didn't think so.

03:16.080 --> 03:20.670
♪♪

03:20.670 --> 03:22.040
[ Horn honks ]

03:27.170 --> 03:29.000
Drive! Go, go, go!

03:29.000 --> 03:30.040
Did you just try
to pull off

03:30.040 --> 03:31.460
one last heist before
retirement,

03:31.460 --> 03:32.830
but the crew member
you trusted the most

03:32.830 --> 03:34.920
turned out to be working for
the feds the entire time?

03:34.920 --> 03:37.120
What?! No! I just
want to leave -- now!

03:37.120 --> 03:38.210
Punch it!

03:40.250 --> 03:42.710
Seriously, Oliver,
what is going on?

03:42.710 --> 03:44.460
Did something happen
in ballet?

03:44.460 --> 03:46.250
No, I just want to go.

03:46.250 --> 03:48.250
If you won't talk...

03:48.250 --> 03:50.080
then I'm gonna ask
your teacher.

03:53.500 --> 03:55.460
[ Click, click ]

03:55.460 --> 03:57.040
[ Click, click ]

03:57.040 --> 03:58.420
[ Rapid clicking ]

03:58.420 --> 04:05.750
♪♪

04:05.750 --> 04:07.420
Fine. You win.
Let's go home.

04:07.420 --> 04:09.080
[ Laughs ] Sucker!

04:09.080 --> 04:11.040
Let this be a lesson to you --
trust no one.

04:11.040 --> 04:13.670
Not even your
own mother.
That's a terrible
lesson!

04:15.290 --> 04:16.670
Excuse me, Nina?

04:18.380 --> 04:21.080
Oliver has been acting
a little weird,

04:21.080 --> 04:22.380
and I was wondering
if it's something

04:22.380 --> 04:23.830
that I should
know about.

04:23.830 --> 04:25.790
Actually,
there was...an incident.

04:27.040 --> 04:29.080
Oliver was paired up
with Gina Tuscadero.

04:29.080 --> 04:31.750
[ Gasps ] The granddaughter
of Pinky Tuscadero,

04:31.750 --> 04:34.920
which would make her
Leather Tuscadero's grand-niece?

04:34.920 --> 04:37.380
Pinky and Leather are fictional
characters from "Happy Days."

04:37.380 --> 04:38.920
Gina is a real person.

04:38.920 --> 04:40.460
Well, you're no fun.

04:40.460 --> 04:42.920
Oliver and Gina
were practicing lifts.

04:42.920 --> 04:46.790
[ Classical music plays ]

04:46.790 --> 04:49.750
And right in front
of the class...

04:53.250 --> 04:55.000
...he kind of got
a lift in his pants...

04:55.000 --> 04:56.250
[ Laughter ]

04:56.250 --> 04:57.750
...if you know
what I mean.

04:57.750 --> 04:59.830
Oliver chubbed out?

04:59.830 --> 05:02.540
Yes. That's what I mean.

05:04.580 --> 05:09.120
We're not talking about this --
not now, not ever.

05:13.170 --> 05:14.920
A-Are you smiling?

05:16.710 --> 05:17.920
No.

05:20.880 --> 05:23.210
Why are you so uptight?

05:23.210 --> 05:25.540
I am your mother.
I used to bathe you.

05:25.540 --> 05:27.380
Yeah, well, I got
new stuff since then.

05:27.380 --> 05:29.330
♪♪

05:29.330 --> 05:32.290
Oliver, come on!
Let's talk about this.

05:32.290 --> 05:33.210
There's nothing
to discuss.

05:33.210 --> 05:35.170
I'm never going
to ballet again.

05:36.290 --> 05:37.670
What's wrong with him?

05:37.670 --> 05:40.670
Remember the deal we made when
we decided to have kids?

05:40.670 --> 05:43.170
You handle the vagina questions
and I handle the penisy ones?

05:43.170 --> 05:44.170
Exactly.
[ Door opens ]

05:47.120 --> 05:49.500
We had the best
playdate ever.

05:49.500 --> 05:51.040
Anna-Kat, tell your mom
about it,

05:51.040 --> 05:53.040
and don't leave out
any detail.

05:53.040 --> 05:54.710
Well, we went
to the petting zoo.

05:54.710 --> 05:56.380
That sounds like fun.

05:56.380 --> 05:58.960
It was fun, but then I learned
some pretty disturbing things

05:58.960 --> 06:00.120
about where meat
comes from.

06:00.120 --> 06:02.250
Oh, no.
Oh, yes.

06:02.250 --> 06:04.080
And after talking it out
with Mrs. Summers...

06:04.080 --> 06:05.210
That's me.
[ Giggles ]

06:05.210 --> 06:07.210
...I've decided
to become a vegan.

06:11.040 --> 06:13.120
You bitch.

06:13.120 --> 06:16.080
Hm. Have fun with your
daughter's new lifestyle.

06:16.080 --> 06:18.960
P.S. -- I literally told her
how the sausage is made.

06:18.960 --> 06:20.710
Bye.

06:20.710 --> 06:22.460
[ Door opens, closes ]

06:22.460 --> 06:24.580
Huh. Anna-Kat's a vegan.

06:30.460 --> 06:31.830
The quiet makes
me nervous.

06:31.830 --> 06:33.750
If she is a vegan,

06:33.750 --> 06:37.210
that means I will have to cook
two meals every meal.

06:37.210 --> 06:38.790
It doubles my workload.

06:38.790 --> 06:40.420
And I don't want to shop
at the weird aisle

06:40.420 --> 06:42.380
in the grocery store.
I hate that aisle!

06:42.380 --> 06:44.290
They sell soup in boxes.
It's unnatural.

06:44.290 --> 06:45.830
They do have nice lotions,
though.

06:45.830 --> 06:47.170
Just when you think you have
everything under control,

06:47.170 --> 06:48.580
your kids change on you.

06:48.580 --> 06:50.920
I don't change!
You don't see me having growth.

06:50.920 --> 06:52.620
I certainly do not.

06:52.620 --> 06:54.540
I'll handle Anna-Kat.
You talk to Oliver.

06:54.540 --> 06:56.170
Got it.

06:56.170 --> 06:58.000
Wait. What's wrong
with Oliver?

06:58.000 --> 07:01.790
He had a moment in ballet class
where he was...

07:01.790 --> 07:04.670
you at my nana's funeral.

07:04.670 --> 07:06.750
We agreed that
was not my fault.

07:06.750 --> 07:09.080
We were packed in like sardines,
and you look sexy in black.

07:09.080 --> 07:10.830
♪♪

07:10.830 --> 07:14.670
Anna-Kat, animals are actually
happy to be eaten.

07:14.670 --> 07:16.040
We're doing them
a solid.

07:16.040 --> 07:18.330
Non-vegan food is full
of hormones, Mama.

07:18.330 --> 07:20.920
Do you want me to get
my period when I'm 9?

07:20.920 --> 07:23.000
I'm gonna kill Tara Summers!

07:23.000 --> 07:25.710
I am a vegan,
I will always be a vegan,

07:25.710 --> 07:29.880
and there is nothing
you can do to change my mind.

07:29.880 --> 07:31.380
I'll give you
10 bucks to stop.

07:31.380 --> 07:33.790
Please.
Ohhhh.

07:33.790 --> 07:35.620
Son, you're an Otto.

07:35.620 --> 07:38.620
That means you're genetically
predisposed to humiliation.

07:38.620 --> 07:41.170
Your cousin Freddy
kissed his own mother

07:41.170 --> 07:43.500
because he panicked on
a kiss cam at a Knicks game.

07:43.500 --> 07:46.000
Your grandfather Reginald
had a lactose issue,

07:46.000 --> 07:47.920
which ultimately
made his roommate,

07:47.920 --> 07:50.040
Donald Whoopie,
millions.

07:50.040 --> 07:52.080
Your great-grandfather
Frederick Otto --
Dad, what's
your point?

07:52.080 --> 07:53.540
My point is,
they didn't let those

07:53.540 --> 07:55.330
embarrassing moments
define them.

07:55.330 --> 07:56.830
Yeah, but it did
define them.

07:56.830 --> 07:58.040
All these years later,

07:58.040 --> 08:00.120
that's all they're
remembered for, right?

08:06.120 --> 08:08.330
I'm gonna need some time
to regroup.

08:11.040 --> 08:13.170
How did it go?
Awful. You?

08:13.170 --> 08:15.420
She almost convinced me
that cheese has feelings.

08:15.420 --> 08:17.540
Had to get out of there.
Well, at least only two

08:17.540 --> 08:19.000
of the three
kids are --
Hey, guys.

08:19.000 --> 08:20.460
What do you think?
[ Chuckles ]

08:20.460 --> 08:22.040
Never mind.
Three for three.

08:22.040 --> 08:23.040
So you like it?

08:23.040 --> 08:25.460
What has gotten into you?

08:25.460 --> 08:27.290
You are not allowed
to dye your hair

08:27.290 --> 08:28.580
without asking
for permission.

08:28.580 --> 08:30.710
Uh, I'm pretty sure I can,
because I just did.

08:30.710 --> 08:32.710
And it's my hair!
That is not your hair!

08:32.710 --> 08:35.170
As long as you live in this
house, it's my hair.

08:35.170 --> 08:36.920
Everything you have
is mine!

08:36.920 --> 08:38.920
Your liver? I'm letting
you borrow it.

08:38.920 --> 08:40.120
You could at least
admit it's cute.

08:40.120 --> 08:41.960
Cute?! It's not cute!

08:41.960 --> 08:44.080
[ Hans Gruber oinks ]

08:44.080 --> 08:46.920
A pig in a skirt --
that's cute!

08:46.920 --> 08:48.920
Ugh! These girls
are killing me!

08:48.920 --> 08:50.830
I need to lie down.

08:50.830 --> 08:52.040
Where are you going?

08:52.040 --> 08:53.170
Target.

08:53.170 --> 08:54.710
♪♪

08:59.460 --> 09:01.290
My girls are growing up
and not bending to my will.

09:01.290 --> 09:04.170
They're forming their
own...opinions.

09:04.170 --> 09:06.120
Ugh. It's your
fault, Katie.

09:06.120 --> 09:07.880
You always ask them
"What's the matter?"

09:07.880 --> 09:09.040
when they're crying.

09:09.040 --> 09:10.580
Personally, Katie,
I don't see what's wrong

09:10.580 --> 09:11.920
with your children
being their own people.

09:11.920 --> 09:13.670
Surprise, surprise.
What?

09:13.670 --> 09:15.290
Taylor is just trying
to be popular,

09:15.290 --> 09:17.620
and Anna-Kat is just
showing some independence.

09:17.620 --> 09:20.750
Who invited lesbian Dr. Phil
to breakfast?

09:20.750 --> 09:23.420
Uh, just because I care
about my kids' feelings...

09:23.420 --> 09:25.250
Yeah, so dumb.

09:25.250 --> 09:27.290
You're dealing with
a full-on uprising.

09:27.290 --> 09:29.170
You can't talk things
through with them.

09:29.170 --> 09:30.620
You need to crush them
before your house

09:30.620 --> 09:32.790
becomes like Angela's.
Um, my house

09:32.790 --> 09:34.670
is a safe space where
everyone is allowed

09:34.670 --> 09:36.750
to openly express
their truths.

09:36.750 --> 09:38.420
[ Both laugh ]

09:38.420 --> 09:39.920
Kids!

09:39.920 --> 09:43.710
I respect that you enjoy
spraying water in the house,

09:43.710 --> 09:45.120
but I've asked you to stop,

09:45.120 --> 09:48.040
and now I'm feeling
a little unheard.

09:48.040 --> 09:49.960
[ Both laugh ]

09:49.960 --> 09:52.420
I can see you're not in a place
to discuss the issue right now,

09:52.420 --> 09:54.210
so we can talk
about it at bedtime.

09:54.210 --> 09:56.540
Which is, as always,
at your discretion.

09:56.540 --> 09:57.580
[ Both laugh ]

09:57.580 --> 09:59.710
So yeah,
I'm a good mother.

10:00.830 --> 10:02.500
But your story
didn't prove --
I'm a good mother.

10:03.540 --> 10:04.710
Mm.

10:04.710 --> 10:06.920
Kids, line up!

10:06.920 --> 10:09.040
[ Door closes ]

10:09.040 --> 10:12.330
You are all going to start
behaving right now.

10:12.330 --> 10:13.670
Okay, Mom, I'll dye
my hair back.

10:13.670 --> 10:14.670
And I'll eat
meat again.

10:14.670 --> 10:16.210
And I'll stop with
the erections.

10:16.210 --> 10:17.170
Yes!

10:17.170 --> 10:18.750
I'm the best mom ever.

10:18.750 --> 10:21.290
So, which passage?

10:21.290 --> 10:23.670
Oh, God!
I must've fallen asleep.

10:23.670 --> 10:26.250
Come on, Katie. What's your
favorite passage?

10:26.250 --> 10:28.250
I don't need
to pick a passage.

10:28.250 --> 10:30.330
I know everything
about this guy.

10:30.330 --> 10:32.120
You don't even
know his name.

10:32.120 --> 10:34.000
You keep calling him
"Rod Stewart Mill."

10:34.000 --> 10:36.330
Mom, my phone's
not working.

10:36.330 --> 10:38.460
Get your keys.
We need to go get a new one.

10:38.460 --> 10:40.000
What is wrong with you?

10:40.000 --> 10:41.330
Why are you just
standing there?!

10:41.330 --> 10:43.170
This is my life,
and I'm being cut off!

10:43.170 --> 10:44.790
I'm missing things!

10:44.790 --> 10:46.000
Well, Taylor,
since you're doing

10:46.000 --> 10:47.500
what you want
with your hair,

10:47.500 --> 10:49.580
I'm doing what I want
with my phone.

10:49.580 --> 10:51.540
You see, it's mine,
because I paid for it,

10:51.540 --> 10:53.670
so I turned
the service off.

10:53.670 --> 10:55.330
You are the worst!

10:56.540 --> 10:57.710
A couple of days
without her cellphone --

10:57.710 --> 11:00.170
that just might do it.
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

11:00.170 --> 11:01.830
And just
to be sure...

11:03.330 --> 11:05.000
[ Echoing ]
Where's all my stuff?!

11:05.000 --> 11:06.540
If you're old enough
to dye your own hair,

11:06.540 --> 11:08.580
then you're old enough
to get your own stuff!

11:08.580 --> 11:10.960
You got rid of
all her things?
I did.

11:10.960 --> 11:12.540
Everything? Her bed,
her dresser?

11:12.540 --> 11:14.170
All of it's
in the garage.
How did you --

11:14.170 --> 11:16.170
You know how when a child
is stuck under a car,

11:16.170 --> 11:18.080
a mother's love can give
her superhuman strength?

11:18.080 --> 11:21.120
Turns out, it also kicks in
when a mother's really pissed.

11:21.120 --> 11:22.120
Mm.

11:22.120 --> 11:23.710
And you.

11:23.710 --> 11:26.080
You're coming with me to shop
for your very own dinner.

11:26.080 --> 11:27.620
That sounds like fun.

11:27.620 --> 11:29.170
Sorry, Katie. I just can't
get my head around this.

11:29.170 --> 11:31.000
That dresser's 200 pounds.

11:31.000 --> 11:33.210
Rage, Greg.
It makes me strong.

11:33.210 --> 11:38.170
♪♪

11:40.420 --> 11:42.540
Welcome to Hell.

11:42.540 --> 11:45.580
This aisle is filled with all
sorts of vegan nightmares.

11:45.580 --> 11:47.460
Here's some deodorant
that doesn't work,

11:47.460 --> 11:49.000
something called yeast butter,

11:49.000 --> 11:51.250
and -- ooh -- a guy with
his hair in a bun.

11:51.250 --> 11:54.500
He looks homeless, but he's
spending 15 bucks on hemp milk.

11:54.500 --> 11:56.290
Okay.

11:56.290 --> 11:58.620
For dinner,
I was thinking

11:58.620 --> 12:01.670
I'll just fill this thing
with this slimy stuff.

12:01.670 --> 12:05.040
As long as it didn't have
parents, I'll eat it.

12:05.040 --> 12:06.500
Excuse me.
[ Dramatic note plays ]

12:06.500 --> 12:08.710
Everything in this aisle
is just so natural.

12:08.710 --> 12:10.960
Ugh. I need a bath
and a turkey leg.

12:10.960 --> 12:15.000
Katie Otto,
in my aisle, buying tofu.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.460
Give it a rest, Tara.

12:16.460 --> 12:18.920
No, it's still fun.

12:18.920 --> 12:21.790
Anna-Kat, did you know that
leather comes from cow skin?

12:21.790 --> 12:23.830
Your mother's purse
used to be an animal.

12:25.040 --> 12:28.080
Oh. No.
Not this purse.

12:28.080 --> 12:29.710
Excuse me.

12:29.710 --> 12:31.920
Would you please get that blue
jar of Veganaise for me?

12:31.920 --> 12:33.750
My pleasure.

12:33.750 --> 12:35.790
[ Dramatic note plays ]

12:35.790 --> 12:39.040
No.
It's my pleasure.

12:39.040 --> 12:46.290
♪♪

12:46.290 --> 12:48.330
Sloppy joes?

12:48.330 --> 12:50.250
Sloppy joes
are my favorite.

12:50.250 --> 12:51.420
They are?

12:51.420 --> 12:53.120
Too bad you don't
eat meat anymore.

12:53.120 --> 12:54.960
Your dinner is this.

12:54.960 --> 12:56.710
It's called brown-loaf.

12:56.710 --> 12:59.880
And it tastes exactly
like it sounds.
Yuck.

12:59.880 --> 13:00.960
Hey, you should picture that
next time

13:00.960 --> 13:02.380
you lift Gina Tuscadero.

13:03.880 --> 13:06.250
Okay, Mom.
Ha ha ha.

13:06.250 --> 13:07.750
I get it.

13:07.750 --> 13:10.000
I can't use your plates
or your silverware.

13:10.000 --> 13:12.500
But come on. It's sloppy joes.
I'll make a mess.

13:12.500 --> 13:14.330
Actually, blondie,
you don't get it.

13:14.330 --> 13:16.040
If you're old enough
to dye your hair,

13:16.040 --> 13:18.210
then you're old enough
to make your own dinner
with your own food.

13:19.380 --> 13:20.830
I'm calling
Child Services!

13:20.830 --> 13:21.880
With what?

13:21.880 --> 13:23.080
Ugh!

13:23.080 --> 13:24.750
Uprising crushed.

13:24.750 --> 13:26.460
Opinions and ideas squelched.

13:26.460 --> 13:29.540
Children -- sad.
Mom -- happy.

13:29.540 --> 13:32.040
Husband -- messy.

13:32.040 --> 13:33.960
How does it taste,
Anna-Kat?

13:33.960 --> 13:36.880
Brown and loafy?

13:36.880 --> 13:38.420
It tastes like dirt.

13:38.420 --> 13:40.330
I love dirt.

13:40.330 --> 13:42.210
I just used
the family computer

13:42.210 --> 13:44.290
to order myself a pizza
and an air mattress.

13:44.290 --> 13:46.500
Should be here
in 30 minutes or less.

13:46.500 --> 13:48.290
How the hell
did you do that?

13:48.290 --> 13:49.790
I have some birthday money
saved up,

13:49.790 --> 13:51.170
and the Internet
is awesome.

13:51.170 --> 13:52.170
It is awesome.

13:53.540 --> 13:56.120
The Internet, not that
she outsmarted you.

13:56.120 --> 13:57.750
That's awful.

13:57.750 --> 13:59.290
Brown-loaf awful.

13:59.290 --> 14:01.330
Brown-loaf
is my new favorite.

14:01.330 --> 14:03.080
Wow, Katie, you have
really lost control.

14:04.960 --> 14:05.920
Uggggh.

14:10.210 --> 14:11.290
I cracked down on my kids,
like you suggested,

14:11.290 --> 14:12.750
but it only made them
crappier.

14:12.750 --> 14:14.500
Well, then, you have
to double down.

14:14.500 --> 14:16.710
Give Taylor a one-way
bus ticket to Norwalk.

14:16.710 --> 14:17.920
Let her fend for herself,

14:17.920 --> 14:19.250
live in a box with
her huffer friends,

14:19.250 --> 14:21.170
and she'll come
crawling back.

14:21.170 --> 14:22.620
Now, as for Anna-Kat,
I'm thinking,

14:22.620 --> 14:24.960
uh...dog crate
for a few days,

14:24.960 --> 14:26.960
and then throw in
a hamburger.

14:26.960 --> 14:28.540
Saying things like that
is why those people

14:28.540 --> 14:30.750
came and talked to you
at your house.

14:30.750 --> 14:32.330
You know what I think
you should do --

14:32.330 --> 14:34.710
talk to them -- not as a parent,
but as a person.

14:34.710 --> 14:36.250
Oh, my God,
here we go.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.500
Listen, if you shut your kids
down all the time,

14:38.500 --> 14:40.250
they'll start doing things
behind your back.

14:40.250 --> 14:42.330
My parents gave me
a long leash,

14:42.330 --> 14:43.670
so I felt comfortable
talking to them.

14:43.670 --> 14:45.540
And by the time
I was Taylor's age,

14:45.540 --> 14:47.580
I knew I could tell them
I was gay.

14:47.580 --> 14:50.170
Some of my friends
weren't so lucky.

14:50.170 --> 14:51.830
They hid who they were
and led a secret life,

14:51.830 --> 14:54.290
which sucked for them.

14:54.290 --> 14:57.290
So, sure, your kids need
to know you as a parent,

14:57.290 --> 15:00.380
but at a certain age, they need
to know you as a person.

15:00.380 --> 15:02.580
Give them your heart
and give them your soul,

15:02.580 --> 15:04.500
and they'll know they can
come to you with anything.

15:04.500 --> 15:07.040
♪♪

15:07.040 --> 15:10.250
If Katie wasn't here,
you and I would not be friends.

15:12.380 --> 15:14.380
So, I'm going to stop
taking Doris' advice

15:14.380 --> 15:15.710
and try Angela's way.

15:15.710 --> 15:17.710
I'm gonna embrace the fact
that Taylor's changing

15:17.710 --> 15:19.920
and try talking to her --
like a person.

15:19.920 --> 15:21.710
Hey, if that works on her,
maybe you should try it on me.

15:23.040 --> 15:25.210
Noooo!

15:25.210 --> 15:27.170
Are you gonna try talking
to Oliver again?

15:27.170 --> 15:29.500
Yeah. You know, I finally found
a passage for my reading,

15:29.500 --> 15:31.790
and it inspired me to try to
give him some perspective.

15:32.920 --> 15:34.710
So you inspired yourself?

15:34.710 --> 15:36.750
[ Chuckling ]
Yeah, well...

15:36.750 --> 15:38.920
I guess I did.

15:38.920 --> 15:40.880
Perhaps
you should read it.

15:40.880 --> 15:43.380
It may help you
with Taylor, as well.

15:43.380 --> 15:46.880
Uhhhhhhhhhhh...

15:47.830 --> 15:48.790
Whoa!

15:50.670 --> 15:53.420
You're doing homework without
being forced or threatened?

15:53.420 --> 15:56.000
Yes. See what you've
reduced me to?

15:57.380 --> 16:01.120
I came here to tell you
that when I was your age,

16:01.120 --> 16:03.580
I desperately wanted
a belly ring.

16:03.580 --> 16:06.250
But instead of asking Grandma
for permission,

16:06.250 --> 16:08.380
I had Jill Tate shove
a safety pin

16:08.380 --> 16:09.790
right through
my belly button.

16:09.790 --> 16:11.040
Didn't that hurt?

16:11.040 --> 16:12.120
It would've,
but I was super hi--

16:14.120 --> 16:16.080
I had a super-high pain
tolerance back then.

16:16.080 --> 16:18.330
Uh-huh.
So, anyway,

16:18.330 --> 16:20.880
my piercing got infected,
obviously,

16:20.880 --> 16:22.540
but I couldn't ask
my parents for help.

16:22.540 --> 16:23.580
So what'd you do?

16:23.580 --> 16:25.330
Wore a lot of
baggy shirts.

16:25.330 --> 16:28.250
And eventually, I had to steal
my dog's antibiotics,

16:28.250 --> 16:30.080
which did the trick.

16:30.080 --> 16:33.000
But without his medication,
Duke lost most of his fur.

16:37.120 --> 16:39.380
I'm sorry I dyed my hair
without permission.

16:39.380 --> 16:41.460
Why didn't you come
talk to me first?

16:41.460 --> 16:43.790
Because -- I knew
you would say no.

16:43.790 --> 16:45.380
Sounds like me.

16:45.380 --> 16:46.790
How 'bout this?

16:46.790 --> 16:50.040
I won't automatically
say no to things

16:50.040 --> 16:51.960
if you promise to talk
to me first.

16:51.960 --> 16:53.710
Deal.

16:53.710 --> 16:55.790
So I can keep my hair?
Absolutely not.

16:55.790 --> 16:58.040
That is not grandfathered
into our new understanding.

16:58.040 --> 16:59.170
And even with our new
understanding,

16:59.170 --> 17:00.210
I still would say no.

17:01.830 --> 17:03.040
I don't see what
I've won here.

17:03.040 --> 17:04.170
Very little.

17:05.830 --> 17:07.710
[ Door closes ]

17:07.710 --> 17:09.420
How did it go?
[ Sighs ]

17:09.420 --> 17:11.670
I gave him my best stuff, but
he's still not going to ballet.

17:11.670 --> 17:13.120
[ Hans Gruber oinks ]

17:13.120 --> 17:15.250
Ooh. Suddenly, I feel
underdressed.

17:15.250 --> 17:16.620
[ Oinks ]

17:18.460 --> 17:20.460
Basically, I told Oliver he
shouldn't let embarrassment

17:20.460 --> 17:21.790
stop him from doing
something he loves

17:21.790 --> 17:23.250
and he needs to soldier
through it.

17:23.250 --> 17:24.830
And even though it doesn't
seem like it now,

17:24.830 --> 17:27.500
one day, this will all
just be a funny story
he tells at parties.

17:27.500 --> 17:29.670
I've got a much shorter story
about my talk with Taylor.

17:29.670 --> 17:30.710
I crushed it!

17:30.710 --> 17:32.380
[ Oinking ]

17:36.000 --> 17:37.540
Who's doing this?

17:37.540 --> 17:40.250
♪♪

17:40.250 --> 17:42.880
My reading is in an hour!
I can't find any of my belts!

17:42.880 --> 17:44.580
Leather belts are made
out of animals,

17:44.580 --> 17:46.670
so I gave them all
a proper burial.

17:46.670 --> 17:47.790
[ Sighs ]

17:47.790 --> 17:49.620
I will help you
kill Tara Summers.

17:49.620 --> 17:53.380
Okay. But I want this face
to be the last one she sees.

17:53.380 --> 17:55.120
Honey, you look great.
Don't worry.

17:55.120 --> 17:58.960
Kids,
I made a new recipe --

17:58.960 --> 18:00.290
veggie chicken.

18:01.830 --> 18:03.380
What's it made out of?

18:03.380 --> 18:04.210
Tofu.

18:05.960 --> 18:08.040
And what's the bone
made out of?

18:10.290 --> 18:11.750
Also tofu.

18:14.750 --> 18:17.000
Even though I have to talk
things out more with Taylor,

18:17.000 --> 18:18.580
Anna-Kat is 8.

18:18.580 --> 18:20.040
I don't have to treat her
like a person.

18:20.040 --> 18:22.330
Lying to her works just fine.

18:22.330 --> 18:28.460
♪♪

18:28.460 --> 18:30.250
Good crowd.

18:30.250 --> 18:31.750
And that's why
I love you.

18:36.670 --> 18:38.460
Good evening.

18:38.460 --> 18:41.040
My name is Gregory Otto,
and I am the author.

18:41.040 --> 18:44.290
I'd like to begin the evening
with a reading from my book

18:44.290 --> 18:46.420
"John Stuart Mill
and the Consequences

18:46.420 --> 18:48.380
of a Thoroughgoing
Empiricist Outlook."

18:50.460 --> 18:53.540
"London, 1806.

18:53.540 --> 18:56.580
A philosopher is born."

18:56.580 --> 18:59.210
It's too bad the advice Greg
gave Oliver didn't work,

18:59.210 --> 19:01.170
because it was spot-on.

19:01.170 --> 19:02.380
"...John's father,

19:02.380 --> 19:04.790
historian and political theorist
James Mill..."

19:04.790 --> 19:07.920
Oh, my God.
It's just like "The Matrix."

19:07.920 --> 19:10.120
Oliver can't be told how to
soldier through embarrassment.

19:10.120 --> 19:12.540
He has to see it for himself.

19:12.540 --> 19:14.380
"...all it knows from
the external world.

19:14.380 --> 19:16.880
Whatever pleasure is derived
from internal processes

19:16.880 --> 19:19.580
can be attribute to
the external stimuli.

19:19.580 --> 19:20.830
The --"

19:20.830 --> 19:22.790
[ Crowd murmuring ]

19:31.670 --> 19:33.420
[ Clears throat ]

19:33.420 --> 19:36.960
"Mill's canonical work
on utilitarianism,

19:36.960 --> 19:40.500
aptly entitled 'Utilitarianism',

19:40.500 --> 19:43.790
argues for a thoroughgoing
empiricist, himself,

19:43.790 --> 19:46.250
a trait inherited from Bentham
and all other conclusions..."

19:46.250 --> 19:47.290
Thank you.

19:49.960 --> 19:52.420
I get what you did.

19:52.420 --> 19:54.120
You were publicly embarrassed,
but you didn't quit.

19:55.540 --> 19:56.830
Yep.

19:56.830 --> 19:59.170
That's...why I had
your mother do that.

20:00.460 --> 20:01.670
So you're not gonna
quit ballet?

20:01.670 --> 20:04.710
No. I'm just gonna
triple up on tights.

20:08.170 --> 20:09.420
You.

20:09.420 --> 20:10.880
What?

20:10.880 --> 20:12.250
We talked about
one of us

20:12.250 --> 20:13.620
embarrassing ourselves
to make a point.

20:13.620 --> 20:15.420
Did you really think
it was going to be me?

20:15.420 --> 20:18.460
I thought maybe, but I live a
whole secret life in my head.

20:18.460 --> 20:20.250
I thought you sounded
great out there.

20:20.250 --> 20:22.080
And when your book
comes out on tape,

20:22.080 --> 20:23.170
I'm gonna read it.

20:23.170 --> 20:24.540
Aww. Thanks, honey.

20:24.540 --> 20:26.920
I mean that now.
Can't imagine I will.

20:30.710 --> 20:33.790
[ Grunting ]

20:33.790 --> 20:36.540
Anna-Kat, are you sure
this is the place?

20:36.540 --> 20:38.120
Honestly,
I don't remember.

20:38.120 --> 20:40.290
You put me on the spot,
and I pointed.

20:40.290 --> 20:42.750
Why don't you just
buy a new belt?

20:42.750 --> 20:45.040
I'm not buying a new belt when
there's a perfectly good belt

20:45.040 --> 20:48.290
buried somewhere
in this backyard.

20:48.290 --> 20:50.330
Ugh!

20:50.330 --> 20:52.080
Oh, my -- Greg!

20:55.080 --> 20:57.170
See, Oliver? Another
classic Otto story.

20:57.170 --> 20:57.960
[ Gasps ]
Ooh!

21:00.040 --> 21:02.460
That's it.
I'm not having kids.

21:02.460 --> 21:04.500
This madness ends with me.

21:04.500 --> 21:06.290
♪♪
